# Public marketing site (Next.js)
# Local: run website + portal together: `npm run dev:with-portal` (portal opens in new tab from "Client portal").
# Or run `npm run dev` and separately `npm --prefix law-firm-portal/frontend run dev`.
# Production: root `.env.production` is loaded by Next and by `scripts/run-portal-build.mjs` (VITE_* for embedded portal).
# For secrets on a public repo, use Vercel env vars instead, or use gitignored `.env.production.local` locally.
# Same-domain portal: leave NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL unset; "Client portal" links to /portal/login.
# Override portal origin only if the portal is hosted on a different domain:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL=http://localhost:5173
# Legacy mono proxy: `npm run dev:mono` sets NEXT_PUBLIC_PORTAL_URL in the script.
